==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Samson
<hw>Sam"son</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An Israelite of Bible
record (see <au>Judges xiii.</au>), distinguished for his great
strength; hence, a man of extraordinary physical strength.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Samson post</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<cd>A strong post resting on the keelson, and supporting a beam of the
deck; also, a temporary or movable pillar carrying a leading block or
pulley for various purposes.</cd> <au>Brande & C.</au> <sd>(b)</sd>
<cd>In deep-well boring, the post which supports the walking beam of the
apparatus.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Samurai</ent>⟦br⟧
